Package org.unibl.etf.epj2.vehicles

Class ReadVehicles

java.lang.Object
org.unibl.etf.epj2.vehicles.ReadVehicles
public class ReadVehicles extends Object
This class is responsible for reading vehicle data from a CSV file and loading them into a set of Vehicle objects. The class contains constants that represents different types of vehicles and separators used in the CSV file.

This class utilizes the RentalCalculator class to retrieve the file path of the CSV file containing vehicle data.

Author:
Tamara Kosovac

  • Method Details

    • readVehicles

      public static Set<Vehicle> readVehicles()
      Static method for loading vehicles from a CSV file. The method reads the file, parses each line and creates appropriate Vehicle object based on the vehicle type.

      If the vehicle type is unrecognized, the line is ignored. Duplicate vehicles (identified by the vehicle ID) are also ignored.

      Returns:
      A set of Vehicle objects loaded from the CSV file.
